######## Problem1 ----->  Consecutive Numbers ###################################
link -----> https://leetcode.com/problems/consecutive-numbers/?envType=study-plan-v2&id=top-sql-50


Q. Write an SQL query to find all numbers that appear at least three times consecutively.

with similar as (
select num,
lead(num,1) over() num1,
lead(num,2) over() num2
from logs
)

select distinct num as ConsecutiveNums from similar 
where num = num1 and num = num2


######## Problem2 ----->  Replace Employee ID With The Unique Identifier ###################################
link -----> https://leetcode.com/problems/replace-employee-id-with-the-unique-identifier/?envType=study-plan-v2&id=top-sql-50


Q. Write an SQL query to show the unique ID of each user, If a user does not have a unique ID replace just show null.


select e.name,em.unique_id
from employees e
left join employeeUNI em on e.id = em.id


